24/01/21, 1:17 pm - Shiuli Subhra Ghosh: Dear First-Year Students of the MSc Data Science program:

Recently, I received a series of emails with several kinds of questions. I am happy to address your request and guide you. However, some issues come to my notice, and I believe, I should address these issues.

1) During the 'open house'; we explained to you several times that this program aimed at the students who are aspiring for a corporate career. This program will not prepare you for the traditional Ph.D. program of Computer Science or Statistics. However, several of you contacted me personally expressing the interest that you want to pursue a Ph.D. abroad. I understand it is your life, your career, and your choice. But you should not expect that this program will prepare you for a Ph.D. program.

2) Some of you asked me if you can do any academic summer internship. So that you can build your profile; apply for the Ph.D. program and secure a letter of recommendation from that professor. My answer is academic internship is strongly discouraged in this program. If you are hoping to do an academic internship you are in the wrong program.

3) In addition, some of you expressed interest to write a research paper with me. Again let me tell you, this is not a Ph.D. program. This is the "Marsters" program. You should focus on mastering the material that we are trying to teach you in this program. When you will do a Ph.D., (if you pursue Ph.D.), it will be your Ph.D. advisor's responsibility to teach you "How to do research!" and "How to write a research paper!" Since I am not your Ph.D. advisor, I do not have any obligation to write a research paper with you. First, you should learn the foundation of Data Science before you do research. These four-semesters; you should focus on building your foundations of data science.


In case, you can't secure a corporate job and decide to go to the USA to do a Ph.D.; you simply do the following steps and trust me you will reach your dreamland.

Step 1: Try to secure an "A" grade in three different subjects with three different professors. Then check with the professor if she or he will write a letter for you. I hope the prof will write for you unless prof thinks you are a smart ass.

Step 2: Secure good score in GRE, Toefl and Math GRE

Step 3: Apply several places - you will get it from at least one place - then fly away.

I understand perhaps some of you were trying to impress me with the hope that I will write a letter of recommendation for you. Let me tell you this, I am already impressed with you because all of you did really well in your CMI admission test. Perhaps now it is time you should focus on the program.

My policy is very clear. If I teach you any course, you secure an "A" grade and if I believe you are not a "smart ass", I will write a letter for you. You don't have to write a research paper with me.

I hope I cleared myself abundantly and if I receive any more requests for writing a research paper - I will assign a few more assignments along with what you already have.

Thanks for your attention. Enjoy your weekend.

Sourish
Associate Professor
Chennai Mathematical Institute, INDIA
https://www.cmi.ac.in/~sourish/
